<h3>Feild sets</h3>
<p>With fieldsets you can group related fields together, also add helper text to the start of a form where an expected pattern may have changed, in this example the optional fields as apposed to required.</p>


<div class="hightlight example">
    <form class="highlight highlight_tertiary form_large shrinko" action="/">
        <fieldset>
            <div class="field_container">
                <p class="form_help">All fields are required except those marked optional.</p>
            </div>
        </fieldset>
        <fieldset>
            <div class="field_container">
                <label for="first_name">Name</label>
                <div class="field">
                    <input type="text" id="first_name" aria-required="true" class="">
                </div>
            </div>
        </fieldset>
        <fieldset>
            <div class="field_container">
                <label for="first_name">Address</label>
                <div class="field">
                    <textarea id="bio" placeholder="" rows="5"></textarea>
                </div>
            </div>
        </fieldset>
        <fieldset>
            <div class="field_container">
                <label for="first_name">Email
                    <em>(optional)</em>
                </label>
                <div class="field">
                    <input type="text" id="first_name" aria-required="true" class="">
                </div>
            </div>
        </fieldset>
    </form>
</div>

